name: Donald Trump
summary: Multiple news articles focus on recent events surrounding former US President Donald Trump. An explosive revelation by his niece in TIME alleges that Trump callously suggested that disabled people like her son "should just die." In an opinion piece, The New York Times highlights the growing frustration of Trump with strong women. Meanwhile, the FBI has secured Trump's agreement to be interviewed as part of an investigation into the assassination attempt against him, as reported by The Associated Press. Two rally attendees injured in the incident have now been released from the hospital, according to NBC News. ABC News reports that the shooter was observed flying a drone near the shooting site hours before the event. Despite his popularity on TikTok, Republicans remain hesitant to follow his lead, notes NPR. CNN and BBC report that the FBI plans to seek Trump's perspective in the ongoing shooting probe. Al Jazeera English investigates conservative claims about Google allegedly covering up the assassination attempt, while The New York Times reveals that the gunman managed to outmaneuver the Secret Service leading up to the shooting.

name: Earthquake
summary: A series of earthquakes have occurred in the past several hours, affecting different regions of the United States. A magnitude-4.9 earthquake shook parts of Southern California, with aftershocks following the initial tremor. West Texas experienced a 5.1-magnitude earthquake, which was declared a disaster due to reported damage. A 4.9-magnitude earthquake struck near Barstow, California, and was felt in Las Vegas. A magnitude-3.3 earthquake occurred near Fairfield, Northern California. A 4.9-magnitude earthquake in California was also felt in Las Vegas. In Texas, San Angelo reported feeling an earthquake. Additionally, a small earthquake was recorded near Gardiner, Maine.

name: North Korea
summary: North Korea has been actively engaged in cyber espionage, according to the NSA and other agencies. Despite economic struggles, South Korea estimates that North Korea's economy grew in 2023. Concerns have arisen regarding Kim Jong Un's health, with officials seeking medication for obesity-related issues. South Korea has increased propaganda broadcasts at the border after North Korea sent trash balloons across the boundary. Notably, a cyber firm hired a North Korean IT worker who turned out to be fake. North Korea has experienced heavy rainfall, prompting the mobilization of troops for rescue efforts. Recent reports reveal details about Kim Jong Un's succession plan, while South Korea's presidential compound was hit by a trash balloon from North Korea. Lastly, thousands have been stranded in North Korea due to flooding, leading to an emergency declaration by Kim.

name: White Dudes for Harris
summary: "White Dudes for Harris" is a group supporting Vice President Kamala Harris' presidential campaign. Despite its controversial name, which has drawn criticism for its apparent exclusion, the group has attracted thousands of members and raised millions of dollars. The gatherings, held over Zoom, aim to provide a space for white men to acknowledge their role in systemic racism and support Harris as a symbol of change. The group's name is intended to reclaim masculinity and challenge the perception that it is associated solely with the far right.

summary: Two former LSU volleyball players, Kristen Nuss and Taryn Kloth, have embarked on an extraordinary journey that led them to the Olympic Games in Paris. Both players made history in their Olympic debuts, with Kloth securing a 2-0 victory for Creighton and Kloth becoming the first Sioux Falls native to win a match at the Olympics. Their remarkable story, from teammates at LSU to Olympic competitors, has garnered significant attention and admiration. Nuss and Kloth's unwavering determination and talent have propelled them to the top of their sport, making them an inspiration and role model for aspiring athletes.

name: Julio Foolio
summary: Jacksonville rapper Julio Foolio was fatally shot in an ambush in Tampa, Florida. One month later, three suspects have been arrested in connection with his murder. The surveillance video of the incident, released by law enforcement, shows the suspects ambushing Foolio and opening fire. Two additional suspects remain at large and are wanted for questioning. Authorities believe the shooting was gang-related, with the arrested individuals being members of a rival gang. The investigation is ongoing, and further updates are expected as the case progresses.
